- desc: The tile source used when rendering the tile map. The type of the property
    is hash.
  name: tile_source
  type: property
- desc: The material used when rendering the tile map. The type of the property is
    hash.
  name: material
  type: property
- desc: Functions and messages used to manipulate tile map components.
  members:
  - desc: 'Replace a tile in a tile map with a new tile.

      The coordinates of the tiles are indexed so that the "first" tile just

      above and to the right of origin has coordinates 1,1.

      Tiles to the left of and below origin are indexed 0, -1, -2 and so forth.


      <pre>

      +-------+-------+------+------+

      |  0,3  |  1,3  | 2,3  | 3,3  |

      +-------+-------+------+------+

      |  0,2  |  1,2  | 2,2  | 3,2  |

      +-------+-------+------+------+

      |  0,1  |  1,1  | 2,1  | 3,1  |

      +-------O-------+------+------+

      |  0,0  |  1,0  | 2,0  | 3,0  |

      +-------+-------+------+------+

      </pre>


      The coordinates must be within the bounds of the tile map as it were created.

      That is, it is not possible to extend the size of a tile map by setting tiles
      outside the edges.

      To clear a tile, set the tile to number 0. Which tile map and layer to manipulate
      is identified by the URL and the layer name parameters.


      Transform bitmask is arithmetic sum of one or both FLIP constants (`tilemap.H_FLIP`,
      `tilemap.V_FLIP`) and/or one of ROTATION constants

      (`tilemap.ROTATE_90`, `tilemap.ROTATE_180`, `tilemap.ROTATE_270`).

      Flip always applies before rotation (clockwise).'
    name: set_tile
    parameters:
    - desc: the tile map
      name: url
      type:
      - string
      - hash
      - url
    - desc: name of the layer for the tile
      name: layer
      type:
      - string
      - hash
    - desc: x-coordinate of the tile
      name: x
      type: number
    - desc: y-coordinate of the tile
      name: y
      type: number
    - desc: index of new tile to set. 0 resets the cell
      name: tile
      type: number
    - desc: optional flip and/or rotation should be applied to the tile
      name: transform-bitmask
      optional: true
      type: number
    type: function
  - desc: 'Get the tile set at the specified position in the tilemap.

      The position is identified by the tile index starting at origin

      with index 1, 1. (see [ref:tilemap.set_tile()])

      Which tile map and layer to query is identified by the URL and the

      layer name parameters.'
    name: get_tile
    parameters:
    - desc: the tile map
      name: url
      type:
      - string
      - hash
      - url
    - desc: name of the layer for the tile
      name: layer
      type:
      - string
      - hash
    - desc: x-coordinate of the tile
      name: x
      type: number
    - desc: y-coordinate of the tile
      name: y
      type: number
    returns:
    - desc: index of the tile
      type: number
    type: function
  - desc: 'Get the bounds for a tile map. This function returns multiple values:

      The lower left corner index x and y coordinates (1-indexed),

      the tile map width and the tile map height.


      The resulting values take all tile map layers into account, meaning that

      the bounds are calculated as if all layers were collapsed into one.'
    name: get_bounds
    parameters:
    - desc: the tile map
      name: url
      type:
      - string
      - hash
      - url
    returns:
    - desc: x coordinate of the bottom left corner
      type: number
    - desc: y coordinate of the bottom left corner
      type: number
    - desc: number of columns (width) in the tile map
      type: number
    - desc: number of rows (height) in the tile map
      type: number
    type: function
  - desc: Sets the visibility of the tilemap layer
    name: set_visible
    parameters:
    - desc: the tile map
      name: url
      type:
      - string
      - hash
      - url
    - desc: name of the layer for the tile
      name: layer
      type:
      - string
      - hash
    - desc: should the layer be visible
      name: visible
      type: boolean
    type: function
  - desc: flip tile horizontally
    name: H_FLIP
    type: number
  - desc: flip tile vertically
    name: V_FLIP
    type: number
  - desc: rotate tile 90 degrees clockwise
    name: ROTATE_90
    type: number
  - desc: rotate tile 180 degrees clockwise
    name: ROTATE_180
    type: number
  - desc: rotate tile 270 degrees clockwise
    name: ROTATE_270
    type: number
  name: tilemap
  type: table
